To visualise data, the untransformed indicators for 1990 and 2019, respective uncertainty intervals and percent changes were presented in Table 2. The scaled or transformed indicators and the SDG index were arranged in Table 3
                        , using colour coding representing three ranges of values: (a) darkest shade of grey for values from 0 to 49 indicating low performance; (b) medium shade of grey for values from 50 to 69 indicating medium performance; and (c) lightest shade of grey for values between 70 and 100 indicating good performance. This conditional formatting followed Microsoft Excel's default ‘color scales’ formatting. Point estimates were presented in this paper by every five years, from 1990 to 2019, to contribute to the assessment of changes that occurred in the period in a more detailed approach (Table 4
                        ).
